SCRAPIE, SHEEP - SLOVENIA
************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 14 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE), Emergency Alert Messages
[edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/040712SVN.htm>

Scrapie in Slovenia
---------------------
(Disease never reported before in Slovenia).
Information received on 9 Jul 2004 from Dr. Simona Salamon, Acting Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Food, Ljubljana:
Date of the report: 9 Jul 2004.
A case of transmissible spongiform encephalopathy was laboratory-diagnosed
in a ewe, which was from a farm where there were 18 other sheep.
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary Institute,
Ljubljana. The sample was also sent to the European Union Reference Laboratory.
Diagnostic tests used:
- Enfer Technology and Prionics-Check rapid tests;
- histopathological examination;
- immunohistochemical examination.
Epidemiology: detailed epizootiological investigation is in progress.
Control measures:
- ban on movements;
- stamping out will be carried out.
[Slovakia reported the disease in 2003, but the incidence, by country, is
not as high in Eastern Europe as it is in the rest of Europe. - Mod.PC]
